      },
      "date": "2011-11-28 10:22:04.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\n(1 inline comment)\n\nBruce, I would love to land this patch, but I'm unclear why you are merging multiple unrelated changes together.\n\nThe first part of this change relates to obdfilter-survey (for which I would use component \"iokit:\", see http://wiki.whamcloud.com/display/PUB/Commit+Comments for other component examples). It isn't so bad that there are several minor fixes to the iokit code in one patch. However, the change to lustre-core.m4 has nothing to do with iokit or the other fixes in this patch that I can see, and is just an unrelated cleanup that was attached to this patch. Describing both of the fixes in the same commit comment (which is itself good), doesn't make the two changes related.\n\nAlso, the bug LU-483 \"Lustre quota not usable\" doesn't have anything to do with either iokit or lustre-core.m4 that I can see.\n\nPlease, one fix per patch, and this needs to be submitted against a valid bug report.  This makes it easier to track the reason for each change, and avoids delaying landing one fix because a problem was found with the other fix.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
